entries.title: Expensive cars, a swimming pool and security guards - Tate's lavish home may have to pay for his legal woes
entries.description: We drive down a dusty street in the northern suburbs of Bucharest.

entries.title: Two years after the Capitol riots in the US - Brazil now faces the reality democracy can be very fragile
entries.description: Police officers in a 4x4 pulled up next to us as we filmed in the Three Powers Plaza in Brasilia.

entries.title: Family of British volunteer missing in Ukraine: 'We are very worried right now'
entries.description: The family of one of the British aid workers missing in Ukraine have said they are "very worried and concerned" about his health and whereabouts.

entries.title: Missing Briton reveals how he dodged drones and bombs while helping evacuate people from Bakhmut
entries.description: One of the Britons missing in Ukraine revealed in his last interview before he vanished the kind of danger he and his fellow volunteers face on a daily basis.

entries.title: Syrian refugee whose story inspired Netflix drama goes on trial in 'farcical' human smuggling case
entries.description: A Syrian refugee and competitive swimmer whose story inspired a Netflix film has gone on trial in a smuggling-related case after participating in migrant rescue operations on a Greek island.

entries.title: 'There's almost no life left': Russia steps up attacks as troops attempt to encircle major Donetsk city
entries.description: Russia has stepped up its offensive in Ukraine, with officials suggesting Vladimir Putin's troops have taken control of an area outside the major city of Bakhmut.

entries.title: Last summer was Europe's hottest ever
entries.description: Last summer was Europe's hottest on record by a clear margin, new data shows.

entries.title: At least 17 killed in Peru as anti-government protests escalate near airport
entries.description: At least 17 people have been killed in anti-government clashes between protesters and police in southern Peru, according to officials.

entries.title: 'It could detonate at any time': Surgeon removes 'live grenade' from inside soldier's body
entries.description: A surgeon in Ukraine has removed a live grenade from inside a soldier's chest, the country's military has said.

entries.title: Bolsonaro shares photo of himself in hospital after supporters storm Brazil's Congress
entries.description: Jair Bolsonaro has shared a picture of himself in hospital as he received treatment in the US, a day after his supporters ransacked Brazil's Congress.

entries.title: Boy, 6, who shot teacher used mother's gun - as police reveal more details of shooting
entries.description: A six-year-old pupil who shot his teacher used a gun that belonged to his mother and was legally owned, police have said.

entries.title: China halts visas for South Koreans in retaliation for COVID travel curbs
entries.description: China has suspended issuing short-term visas for South Koreans, in the first retaliatory move against countries imposing COVID curbs on Chinese travellers.

entries.title: Controversial influencer Andrew Tate loses appeal against continued arrest in Romania
entries.description: A court in Romania has upheld the 30-day arrest of influencer Andrew Tate on charges of organised crime, human trafficking and rape.

entries.title: Magnificent buildings in Brazil are pockmarked by rioting - amid fears the unrest may not be over
entries.description: The magnificent stark white modernist buildings of Brazil's capital were unveiled in the 1960s as a modern utopia and a symbol of optimism and trust in the future.

entries.title: Andrew Tate appears in court over rape and human trafficking charges
entries.description: Andrew Tate and his brother Tristan are back in court today, asking to be set free from detention in Romania.

entries.title: Andrew Tate to appear in court later today - and is expected to ask to be freed from detention
entries.description: Andrew Tate and his brother Tristan will be back in court this morning - asking to be set free from detention in Romania. And around the world, many will be waiting to see what happens next.
